Hi A2A community,

I would like join this discussion with follow proposal point, Looking forward to your feedback and suggestions.

## Muiltple Namespace Proposal

Namespaces can be used in various scenarios for strong isolation, such as different tenants and environments. I strongly agree with the previous discussion and believe this is a capability that registries should provide.

However, regarding how namespaces are passed in the API, I think using a RESTful approach and placing them in the path would be cluttered. So I think it's better to place the namespace parameter in the query, for example.

```
GET URL: https://<registry-url>/agents/entitled?namespace=xxx
```

If no namespace parameter is passed, the default namespace or all agents with permissioned namespaces will be used.

## Muiltple version Proposal

Currently, the AgentCard contains a version field to indicate the current Agent version, but the registry only provides a URL for retrieving the AgentCard. Does this mean that the registry is unaware of the Agent version information? Instead, the Agent client uses this URL to retrieve a random AgentCard version (assuming multiple versions are running concurrently or newer versions are being released).

This random retrieval of newer and older AgentCard versions is not a major issue if the newer Agent version is fully compatible with the older one. However, if blocking changes occur, such as deleting a skill, this could cause exceptions or incorrect results when the upstream agent calls the downstream agent.

Therefore, I think the registry should be aware of the agent version attribute and expose all supported versions when discovering an agent. Therefore, I envision the API response to be something like the following:

```json
{
  "registry_version": "0.1",
  "resources": [
    {
      "id": "it-agent",
      "name": "IT Agent",
      // Default agent card url, it can be the latest version or user set default version.
      "location": {
        "url": "https://it.example.com/.well-known/agent.json",
        "type": "agent_card"
      },
      "versions": [
        {
          "version":"1.0.0",
          "location": {
            // Muiltple version agent card url
            "url": "https://it.example.com/v1/.well-known/agent.json",
            "type": "agent_card"
          },
        },
        {
          "version":"2.0.0",
          "location": {
            "url": "https://it.example.com/.well-known/agent.json",
            "type": "agent_card"
          },
        }
      ],
    },
    ...
  ],
  "total_count": 2
}
```

## Publish new agent Proposal

I'd like to propose a simple API design for publishing capabilities for new agents for community discussion:

```
// The basic API url
POST URL: https://<registry-url>/agent/publish
```

```json
// The body schema sample 
{
  "resource": {
    "id":"xxx-agent", // optional, if no custom id, registry should auto-generate such as UUID.
    "name":"xxx Agent", // required, should discuss whether global unique or namespace unique.
    "version": { // required.
      "id": "1.0.0",
      "releaseDate": "2025-mm-dd",
      "latest": true
    },
    "location": { // required.
      "url": "https://xxx.com/.well-known/agents.json",
      "type": "agent_card"
    },
  },
  "namespace": "example_namespace" // optional, if no specify, default into default.
}
```

## Auto register agent by themself and discovery peers directly Proposal

From current A2A protocol design, A2A client get the URL from AgentCard or from additionalInterfaces. If the Agent Server are multiple peers, The developer should register the acutal peer address(ip or host) to the domain.

I consider whether the A2A register can do discovery the agent peers directly as an optional enhance behavior like many mircoservice registries?

In order to implement this feature, There are three parts working need to do:

1. A2A registry should support API to register and deregister peer to Agents.
2. A2A registry should support API to getPeers for target Agents.
3. A2A SDK should support call registry publish agent API and register peer API when agent server start.

I'm not sure this feature whether reasonable for community plan, so I don't do detail proposal, If community thinks the feature should be supported, I can continue to do more details.

